are there any foods you can eat before bed that will make you dream remembering your dreams is more about intentionality and habit than anything else keep a notebook by your bed and try to write your dreams or any fragments of dreams into them every morning after you wake when you first start these will be very fleeting and could be only things like a vague sense like scary or floating or colors smells or just images once you get out of bed and start doing things those dream fragments will pretty much disappear as you start to think about your day ahead so it's important to develop the habit of doing it as you start journaling your dreams they will get more detailed and you will start remembering them much better it will also help to think to yourself the night before i will remember my dreams by setting this intention beforehand you are giving yourself the mindset to remember them in the morning it really does help your mind hold onto the dreams in the morning sleeping pills alcohol and most drugs actually inhibit dreaming yes hallucinogenic drugs can create dreamlike states but these are not actually dreams per se physiologically they aren't the same Out-of-body experience Lucid dreaming Psychedelics, dissociatives and deliriants Dream Diazepam Fitz Hugh Ludlow Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Narcolepsy Kurt Cobain Haibane Renmei Phoebe Buffay's songs The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Theory of conduct A Day in the Life Addiction Vomiting Philosophical skepticism Cannabis (drug) Avenue Q Neuro-linguistic programming Hubert Selby Jr. Freddy's Dead: The Final Nightmare Rapid eye movement Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Skinny Dip Social rule Insomnia Folic acid Jon Secada Emanuel Swedenborg Urinary incontinence The Tracey Ullman Show shorts Philosophy of perception Patrick Star Fecal incontinence Psychosis Illegal drug trade Psychology of religion Oral contraceptive Daylight saving time The Shining (film) USS Seadragon (SS-194) W.I.T.C.H. 